article.description: — Jomaru Brown had 17 points in Coastal Carolina's 66-59 victory against South Dakota on Saturday.
article.headline: Coastal Carolina takes down South Dakota 66-59
article.linkText: Coastal Carolina takes down South Dakota 66-59
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- — Jomaru Brown had 17 points in Coastal Carolina's 66-59 victory against South Dakota on Saturday. Brown also added three steals for the Chanticleers (3-2). Essam Mostafa scored 14 points and added 12 rebounds. Henry Abraham was 5 of 9 shooting (3 for 5 from distance) to finish with 13 points. The Coyotes (3-4) were led in scoring by Kruz Perrott-Hunt, who finished with 17 points and four assists. Mihai Carcoana added 13 points and seven rebounds for South Dakota. Paul Bruns also had 10 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
